Akshay Kumar ( real name Rajiv Hari Om Bhatia , born on September 9 , 1967 ) and is of Punjabi origin and is a popular Bollywood film actor who has been known as an icon hero since the early 90s. . Rajiv Hari Om Bhatia , better known as Akshay Kumar was born on September 9 , 1967 in Amritsar , Punjab . He studied martial arts in Bangkok and worked as a Chef . In 1990 he decided to pursue an acting career in the Bollywood film industry . After that he did many action films and was known as a action hero . Particularly successful were the films with Khiladi ( player ) in the title such as Main Khiladi Tu Anari in 1993 . He has also had success in romantic films . Yash Chopra signed him for his next project in 1994 , Yeh Dillagi opposite Kajol and Saif Ali Khan . He received appreciation for his performance in this film , where he played a romantic role which was different compared to his action roles . He was also nominated for Best Actor award at the Filmfare and Star Screen ceremonies . In 1995 , along with his share of unsuccessful movies , he starred in the film Sabse Bada Khiladi , which was a hit . He proved to have success with the Khiladi series , as in the next year he starred in the fourth hit of film with Khiladi in the title , Khiladiyon Ka Khiladi opposite Rekha and Raveena Tandon , which was one of the highest grossing films of the year . In 1997 , he made an extended guest appearance in Yash Chopra 's hit film Dil To Pagal Hai , for which he was nominated for Best Supporting actor award at the Filmfare . In the same year , he attempted a comedy role with the fifth film in the Khiladi series , Mr and Mrs Khiladi which was unsuccessful. . Along with this film , his next Khiladi films went on to fail at the box office . In 1999 , he received critical acclaim for his roles in the films Sangharsh , and in the box office hit Jaanwar . In 2000 he starred in the comedy Hera Pheri ( 2000 ) which was a success and showcased his talent at doing comedy just as well as action or romantic roles . He also starred in the romantic film Dhadkan later that same year which was also a box office hit. . After the success of Hera Pheri , he starred in many successful comedy films which include Awara Paagal Deewana ( 2002 ) , Mujhse Shaadi Karogi ( 2004 ) and Garam Masala ( 2005 ) . . Apart from his action , comedy and romantic roles he also displayed a flair for dramatic roles in films such as Ek Rishta ( 2001 ) , Bewafaa ( 2005 ) and Waqt : The Race Against Time ( 2005 ) which did fairly well at the box office . In 2006 he starred in a sequel to his hit film Hera Pheri titled Phir Hera Pheri which was also been very successful at the box office . Later that year he starred alongside Salman Khan in the romantic film Jaan - E - Mann which did not do as well as expected at the box office but he got positive reviews for his performance . His forthcoming release is Tashan which marks his comeback to the Yashraj Films Banner after Yeh Dillagi and Dil To 